OL,3,CAmputee hit by train supports new
OL,4,Csafety campaign
OL,6,FA woman who lost her leg when she was
OL,7,Fhit by a train at a level crossing in
OL,8,FFarnborough is backing a new railway
OL,9,Fsafety campaign.
OL,11,FLucy Ruck says it happened during a
OL,12,Fmomentary lapse of concentration as
OL,13,Fshe crossed the track on her way to
OL,14,Fcollege.
OL,16,F"What I hadn't realised was from the
OL,17,Fother direction the fast train was
OL,18,Fcoming through the station at 65mph.
OL,20,F"The next thing I knew, it was right
OL,21,Fin my face.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/4
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
