OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1781089372
OL,3,CAmputee hit by train supports new
OL,4,Csafety campaign
OL,6,F"I threw myself back, as I did, my
OL,7,Fright leg went under the train. That
OL,8,Famputated it and they found it half a
OL,9,Fmile up the track."
OL,11,FIt happened in 1993. The level
OL,12,Fcrossing at Farnborough North Station
OL,13,Fhas since been shut and replaced with
OL,14,Fan overbridge.
OL,16,FNetwork Rail's 'No Second Chances'
OL,17,Fcampaign is aimed at reducing risky
OL,18,Fbehaviour at crossings, especially
OL,19,Fwhen people are distracted, over-
OL,20,Ffamiliar, or misjudge a train's speed
OL,21,Fand distance.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/4
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
